article.headline: Austin Peay 88, Tennessee Tech 64
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Maurice Hampton scored 15 points and Austin Peay used big runs in the first and second halves to take an 88-64 victory over Tennessee Tech on Tuesday night. The win was the 26th straight home victory for the Governors (18-8, 15-0 Ohio Valley Conference). Adrian Henning scored 14 points and Anthony Davis added 13 points and seven assists for Austin Peay. Cameron Crisp and Willie Jenkins both scored 15 points for the Golden Eagles (13-13, 7-8). Tennessee Tech started the game with a 15-2 run in the first six minutes before Austin Peay caught its breath. The Governors chipped away at the lead and ended the half on a 15-3 run to take a 35-26 halftime lead. Tennessee Tech stayed close in the second half, trailing 40-35 with 15:22 to play when the Governors began to pull away. The Golden Eagles pulled within 66-59 with five minutes left on a basket by Jenkins, but Austin Peay closed with a 22-5 run to put the game out of reach. The Governors have clinched their second straight conference title. Austin Peay's home winning streak is its longest since the end of the 1975-76 season and start of the '76-77 season, when the Governors also won 26 in a row.
